00:37:08.008 --> 00:37:11.668
showing from an efficacious dose of 200 milligrams all the way

629
00:37:11.748 --> 00:37:15.408
up to tenfold above that, we really don't see much deviation at

630
00:37:15.508 --> 00:37:18.588
all in that rate of probability of an adverse event.

631
00:37:18.608 --> 00:37:22.588
And so that is the definition of a wide therapeutic index drug.

632
00:37:22.938 --> 00:37:26.898
So this is really fascinating to know that degraders, these very complex,

633
00:37:26.988 --> 00:37:30.958
big molecules that are interacting and bringing proteins together in

634
00:37:31.028 --> 00:37:34.998
a way that they normally don't, are not really causing anything that really is

635
00:37:35.048 --> 00:37:38.848
changing the safety or biology of our patient population, which is an

636
00:37:38.928 --> 00:37:42.888
elderly population that is relatively frail, a population that should

637
00:37:42.968 --> 00:37:46.928
expose safety concerns if they were to be there, certainly at

638
00:37:47.288 --> 00:37:51.068
the doses that we're using. So really exciting to understand that degraders can

639
00:37:51.088 --> 00:37:54.268
achieve a profile that might be more akin to antibodies.

640
00:37:55.588 --> 00:37:58.928
What else did we learn in our clinical practice with this drug?

641
00:37:59.227 --> 00:38:02.948
We have also learned that there really is no association of degraders with QT

642
00:38:03.028 --> 00:38:06.088
prolongation. So this is a parameter that is really

